==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fertility
<hw>Fer*til"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fertilitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>fertilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The state or quality of being fertile or fruitful; fruitfulness;
productiveness; fecundity; richness; abundance of resources; fertile
invention; quickness; readiness; <as>as, the <ex>fertility</ex> of soil,
or of imagination</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>fertility</xex> of
resource.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>E. Everett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And all her husbandry doth lie on heaps⟦br⟧
Corrupting in its own <qex>fertility</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thy very weeds are beautiful; thy waste⟦br⟧
More rich than other climes' <qex>fertility</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fertilization</ent>⟦br⟧
